== Entity Presence ==
'''Level 4''' is devoid of all hostile life. The only life subsisting on the level are humans, certain species of plants, and a plethora of microscopic creatures; things one would typically expect to be in such an environment.

== Colonies and Outposts ==
Currently, there are three recorded large outposts within '''Level 4'''. The two hundred aforementioned minor groups within the level will not be mentioned for sake of intelligibility.

=== Base Opportunity (M.E.G.) ===

* An outpost established by the [[M.E.G.]] to deal with all civilian affairs and establish a significant foothold within '''Level 4''';
* Undocumented member count — estimated to be in the tens of thousands;
* Known for maintaining ample relations with a vast majority of groups within the level, with their main influence being focused on the trade of goods;
* Has a minor military presence in several outposts, with the goal of peacekeeping. They are friendly to most wanderers, though with exceptions regarding affiliation with [[Republic of Aurielle|certain organizations]].

=== B.A.S. (Backrooms Analytical Squadron) ===

* An organization found exclusively in '''Level 4''' with the primary objective of focusing on the exploration of the office’s structure, secrets, and connections to the Frontrooms;
* The group consists of skilled scientists, professionals in the medical field, reporters, and architects;
* The B.A.S. is known for their several discoveries in the Backrooms;
* Known for maintaining good relations with The Maintenance Workers in [[Level 3]];
* They are friendly and open to trade with wanderers, although a lot of them are quite reserved and do not present a welcoming sight for newcomers.

=== S.R.C. (Society of the Red Cross: Natural Sciences and Medicine) ===

* A medicinal and pharmaceutical organization focused primarily on maintaining and providing for the health of wanderers who pass by;
* The group has a current member count of approximately 433, consisting of various divisions of doctors, nurses, physicians, and pharmacists;
* It assists vulnerable wanderers in situations of disaster/crisis by contributing in averting and alleviating suffering in all its forms, protecting health and mental wellbeing, along with cultivating respect toward human dignity;
* Known to stockpile food, medical supplies and other necessary resources in order to help wanderers have a safe time in '''Level 4''';
* They are friendly and welcoming towards anyone who enters in contact with them; up for trade as long as the object the wanderer trades can serve in healing a harmed human being.

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===
There are quite a few places in which one can access '''Level 4''', which are listed below:

* One may enter this level from [[Level 3]] via a metallic door labeled “office sector”;
* Entering a flatly-colored wooden door on [[Level 30]] may lead one to this level;
* Some doors in [[Level 54]]'s [[Level 54#Floor 2|Floor 2]] have a chance of leading to this level;
* Entering a medical office door within [[Level 16]] may lead one to this level;
* Sewer grates on the ceiling of [[Level 34]] may rarely lead one to this level through the floor;
* Extended hallways in [[Level 37]] lacking any water may eventually lead to '''Level 4''';
* Additionally, did you know that certain areas in [[Level 47]] may seamlessly lead to this level?

=== Exits ===
Whilst most exits within '''Level 4''' tend to lead to [[The Void]], certain minor exceptions do exist, which are listed below:

* Scattered doors playing disquieting classical music, which lead to [[Level 5]];
* Trapdoors and ceiling hatches, which lead to [[Level 6]];
* Attempting to enter a vending machine, which has a chance of sending one to [[Level 197]];
* Entering a small room concealed by theatre curtains, which leads one to [[Level 156]];
* As well as scattered emergency exits, which may lead one to [[Level 14]].
* Going through a door with a brass number "6" will lead to [[Level 332]].
